    "created_at": "2015-07-30T18:13:12Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-30T18:13:12Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz I know it's logical on some level, but the situation is that on Windows you can depend on the \"clicked\" event to do stuff like show/hide window, while on OS X behaviour is different and it shows menu.\n\nFrom a user perspective, nobody is going to need the \"clicked\" event when the menu is shown. It makes absolutely no sense for no application.\n\nCan we at least have a \".menuShown\" property in the event or something? Or control over when the tray icon ctx menu shows? E.g. the only way to show it is listen to \"clicked\" and call a function like ev.showCtxMenu() ?\n"
  },
